data.field:
These work the same as [do while loops] only they execute until the condition evaluated is true<BR>
Here's a quick example:<BR>
<PRE>
$value=5;
do{
  print "$value\n";
  $value=$value-1;
} until($value<=10);
</PRE>
<BR>
<BR>
This is executes once and prints out $value;<BR>
5<BR>
Then $value is decremented and becomes 4<BR>
since 4<=10 is true execution of the loop is terminated<BR>
<BR>
Now onto the exciting world of [for loops]
<BR>
